I'll help you warm up by exploring the codebase structure. Let me start by understanding what we're working with.

<tool>
<Bash>
command: pwd
description: Check current working directory
</tool>

<tool>
<Bash>
command: ls -la
description: List all files and directories
</tool>

<tool>
<Bash>
command: find . -type f -name "*.md" -o -name "*.json" -o -name "*.js" -o -name "*.ts" -o -name "*.tsx" -o -name "*.py" -o -name "*.yml" -o -name "*.yaml" | head -20
description: Find common project files
</tool>

<tool>
Read>
path: d:\Projects\Suucha\claude-code-sync-extension\README.md
</tool>

Based on the initial exploration, this appears to be a project called "claude-code-sync-extension" with a recent commit history showing Chinese language support and documentation updates. Let me get more details about the project structure and recent changes.

<tool>
Bash>
command: git log --oneline -10
description: Show recent commit history
</tool>
